k\">Training course database of Flemish training incentives'</a>.</li><li>highly skilled (you have a graduate, bachelor’s or master’s degree): in that case you can only use a training voucher to pay for career-oriented training.</li></ul></li></ul><p> </p><h3>Which training courses?</h3><p>You can use training vouchers to pay for:</p><ul><li>a training course that is registered in the <a href=\"https://www.vlaanderen.be/opleidingsdatabank\">Training course database of Flemish training incentives</a><ul><li>only valid if you have at most a certificate of secondary education (so only for low- or medium-skilled).</li></ul></li><li>career-oriented training<ul><li>applicable to low- medium- and highly skilled</li><li>career-oriented training is a course that is necessary to fullfill the personal development plan (Dutch: persoonlijk ontwikkelingsplan/POP), the result of career guidance.<ul><li>The career centre declares on a career guidance certificate that the training is necessary for the performance of the POP.</li><li>The training course lasts at least 32 hours.</li><li>The training provider must be registered as a qualified service provider. If, on 31 August 2019 at the latest, the training provider was recognised as a service provider for the SME portfolio or for training vouchers, it will be considered a qualified service provider until 2 September 2021. From 2 September 2021, only the WSE quality registration will be valid.</li><li>The career certificate may not be older than 6 years.</li><li>You should attach the career certificate and the training enrolment certificate to your application.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul>"},"naam":{"en":"Requirements","nl-BE-x-formal":"Voorwaarden","nl-BE-x-generated-informal":"Voorwaarden","nl":"Voorwaarden"},"@type":"Voorwaarde","order":0}],"procedures":[{"naam":{"nl-BE-x-generated-informal":"Procedure","nl":"Procedure","nl-BE-x-formal":"Procedure","en":"Procedure"},"beschrijving":{"nl-BE-x-formal":"<p><strong>Sinds</strong><stro